accessibility.text: Anti-pattern Coding
Anti-pattern Coding
Anti-pattern: When new reactive objects are created for every user interaction
Typically happens when a render*() is called within an observe*()
Anti-pattern Coding
Anti-pattern: When new reactive objects are created for every user interaction
Typically happens when a render*() is called within an observe*()
Correct pattern: Change the established reactive values’ values

Using anti-patterns will cause the reactlog graph to become very large

Anti-pattern: When new reactive objects are created for every user interaction
Typically happens when a render*() is called within an observe*()
Correct pattern: Change the established reactive values’ values

Note: Anti-pattern is only encouraged for newly created content. Ex: insertTab()
